body:
The problem is your network. I have a solution: 1. change to another source to pull onnxruntime image; 2.add trust to your source. You can solve this problem with the following command:
pip install onnxruntime -i http://pypi.douban.com/simple/ --trusted-host pypi.douban.com

issue.title: Build failure of onnxruntime Docker container with Vitis-AI

labels.name: build
labels.description: build issues; typically submitted using template

labels.name: ep:VitisAI
labels.description: issues related to Vitis AI execution provider

repository.name: onnxruntime
repository.description: ONNX Runtime: cross-platform, high performance ML inferencing and training accelerator

issue.body:
**Describe the bug**
When trying to build onnxruntime with the Vitis-AI runtime according to the build instructions at https://onnxruntime.ai/docs/reference/execution-providers/Vitis-AI-ExecutionProvider.html, the build fails due to not finding pyxir includes.

The relevant error message is
```
/code/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/vitisai/vitisai_custom_op.cc:22:10: fatal error: pyxir/common/xbuffer.hpp: No such file or directory
   22 | #include <pyxir/common/xbuffer.hpp>
      |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
compilation terminated.
/code/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/vitisai/vitisai_execution_provider.cc:7:10: fatal error: pyxir/pyxir.hpp: No such file or directory
    7 | #include <pyxir/pyxir.hpp>
      |          ^~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~
compilation terminated.
make[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_providers_vitisai.dir/code/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/vitisai/vitisai_custom_op.cc.o] Error 1
make[2]: *** Waiting for unfinished jobs....
CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_providers_vitisai.dir/build.make:75: recipe for target 'CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_providers_vitisai.dir/code/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/vitisai/vitisai_custom_op.cc.o' failed
make[2]: *** [CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_providers_vitisai.dir/code/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/vitisai/vitisai_execution_provider.cc.o] Error 1
CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_providers_vitisai.dir/build.make:89: recipe for target 'CMakeFiles/onnxruntime_providers_vitisai.dir/code/onnxruntime/onnxruntime/core/providers/vitisai/vitisai_execution_provider.cc.o' failed
``` 

**Urgency**
I was planing to evaluate the onnxruntime with Vitis-AI as part of a research project. The project ends September 30th 2021.

**System information**
- OS Platform and Distribution (e.g., Linux Ubuntu 16.04): Ubuntu 18.04.5 LTS (GNU/Linux 5.4.0-80-generic x86_64)
- ONNX Runtime installed from (source or binary): source
- ONNX Runtime version: GitHub repository (current commit hash: `deab284e4cdd2ea57bd322ecf5ac7129b1c34e79`)
- Python version: Python 3.8.5 or 3.6.12 (not sure which of the two versions inside the Docker container is used during the Docker image build)
- Visual Studio version (if applicable): N/A
- GCC/Compiler version (if compiling from source): gcc (Ubuntu 9.3.0-11ubuntu0~18.04.1) 9.3.0 (compiler version inside Docker container)
- CUDA/cuDNN version: N/A
- GPU model and memory: N/A

**To Reproduce**
```
git clone https://github.com/xilinx/vitis-ai
cd vitis-ai/
cd setup/
cd alveo/
sudo ./install.sh 
cd ../../..
cd onnxruntime/dockerfiles/
docker build -t onnxruntime-vitisai -f Dockerfile.vitisai .
```

**Expected behavior**
Successful build of a Docker image of onnxruntime with enabled Vitis-AI execution provider.

**Screenshots**
N/A, will attach build log at the end.

**Additional context**
The problem seems to be with using Python to locate PXIR. Using the system python version in the Docker container, yields
```
docker run -it 7513773fd99d /bin/bash
Vitis-AI /code > which python
/opt/vitis_ai/conda/bin/python
Vitis-AI /code > python -c "import pyxir as px; print(px.get_include_dir()); print(px.get_lib_dir());"
Traceback (most recent call last):
  File "<string>", line 1, in <module>
AttributeError: module 'pyxir' has no attribute 'get_include_dir'
```
and using the same Python that seems to be activated during the Docker image build results in:
```
Vitis-AI /code > conda activate vitis-ai-tensorflow 
(vitis-ai-tensorflow) Vitis-AI /code > python --version
Python 3.6.12 :: Anaconda, Inc.
(vitis-ai-tensorflow) Vitis-AI /code > python -c "import pyxir as px; print(px.get_include_dir()); print(px.get_lib_dir());"
Illegal instruction (core dumped)
```

issue.body:
### Describe the issue

![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/39560035/189062446-7db83c6a-a1d7-44a3-93ba-d7cf5022b1e1.png)
Excuse me I've been using the tutorial to install ONNX and have been unable to resolve these situations
`./build.sh --update --config Release --enable_pybind --build_shared_lib --build --build_wheel --use_tensorrt --tensorrt_home /usr/src/tensorrt --cuda_home /usr/local/cuda --cudnn_home /usr/lib/aarch64-linux-gnu`
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/39560035/189061553-f093ed7a-0e16-4478-abc7-7b596e96a72b.png)
How do I solve this problem?

### Urgency

_No response_
